Aliases allow for custom commands.
Aliases are controlled using the 'alias' command.
div()
Adding an alias
div()
To add an alias, use alias add:
div()
alias add '<alias>' '<command>'
div()
Remember to use apostrophes('') and NOT quotation marks("").
div()
Listing all aliases
div()
To list all aliases, run:
div()
alias list
div()
This will list all aliases in the format '<alias> --> <command>'.
div()
Removing an alias
div()
To remove an alias, use the command:
div()
alias remove '<alias>'
div()